3) Always-on QA (100% coverage) with alerts and coaching signals for supervisors.', 'GenAI', 4, 4, 3, 4, 3, 2, 2, 2, 3.4, 2.4, 'Quick Win', '2025-09-03 17:12:28.629548', 2, 3, '{"All Commercial"}', '{"Customer Servicing"}', '{"Customer Support","Relationship Management","Issue Resolution","Service Delivery"}', '{"All Segments"}', '{UK}', NULL, 'true', 'true', 'active', '2025-09-03 17:12:28.629548', NULL, 'rsa_internal', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Service – Telephony ACW – We have AI summarisation up and working in Call Miner already, there was a project at the start of the year to get this real time so they could use it for notes and save on after call work (ACW). This requires some change in Vodafone and the process had started but stalled. Claims have now assigned a PM to work on it to push through to get the benefit. There is a secondary benefit as it will do in call prompting aka ‘the broker said looking for advice on product coverage – direct to site XXX’. Contact centers handle high volumes with after-the-fact QA and no in-call assist. Although CallMiner + Microsoft Cognitive + Verint are already procured and the solution design exists, the program is not mobilized at scale; value is left on the table.', 'James (Jay) Gregory (Service & Ops).', 'Backlog', 'CallMiner (core), Microsoft Cognitive Services add-in, Verint (desktop/live prompts), contact center telephony & CRM.', 'Medium–High — “just needs mobilizing”; architecture and licenses are in place.', NULL, 'In-year: approx. 6–7 FTE benefit (transcript)
